<p>One of the main invariants of this protocol (as listed in the contest gi=
thub page) is:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The total supply of a subnet must match the total funds locked for that =
specific subnet in the gateway</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The vulnerability explained in detail below leads to a severely inflated=
 circulating supply of the target subnet, in a way that the total funds loc=
ked for a particular subnet will NOT equal the total supply of funds associ=
ated with the subnet.</p>
<p>The vulnerability exists in the function <code>CheckpointingFacet::execB=
ottomUpMsgs()</code>. This function is called by the function <code>commitC=
heckpoint()</code> which ends up getting called when an actor submits a bot=
tom -&gt; top checkpoint for execution in the parent subnet.</p>
