<p>If a caller in a child subnet creates a xnet message with a non-zero val=
ue to call a smart contract in another child subnet, the funds will be burn=
t (or more precisely, sent to void) and a bottom up message will be committ=
ed. The message will then reach the destination and the funds will be trans=
ferred successfully to the target in the destination subnet. The circulatin=
g supply of the child subnet should reflect that fund transfer, but that=E2=
=80=99s not what happens.</p>
