2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.2=
2 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.0=
9.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"=
 fill-rule=3D"evenodd"></path></svg></a>Recommended mitigation steps</h3>
<p>One way to fix this is to add a <code>hash</code> property to the origin=
al message/IPC envelope. This property should be set by the function <code>=
sendContractXnetMessage()</code> and should not change. Then when a receipt=
 is created, the receipt IPC envelope struct should also have that <code>ha=
sh</code> property and have it set to the hash of the original message. The=
n in <code>IpcContract</code> that <code>hash</code> property should be rel=
ied on instead.</p>
<p><strong>Recall confirmed</strong></p>
