<li>The function <code>submitCheckpoint()</code> will end up reverting as a=
 result which should never happen unless it=E2=80=99s a malicious entity ca=
lling the function or as a result of a programming error. This is how botto=
m -&gt; up checkpointing mechanism is halted.</li>
</ol>
<p>There is a typo bug in the line <code>s.collateralSource.transferFunds(p=
ayable(msg.sender), genesisBalance);</code> in the function <code>leave()</=
code> which was reported separately. However, this bug still persists even =
if that bug was fixed because both <code>supplySource</code> and <code>coll=
ateralSource</code> can be native ETH making this exploitable.</p>
<p>This is a complex bug. I will gladly develop a working PoC for this if n=
eeded.</p>
