<p>To fix this issue, the contract should enforce that the <code>FIL</code>=
 value committed covers both the genesis supply and collateral. In practice=
, this means adding a validation in GatewayManagerFacet.register such a sum=
 check on input values:</p>
<p>Require that <code>genesisCircSupply + collateral</code> does not exceed=
 (and ideally equals) the actual <code>FIL</code> provided by the caller. F=
or example, if the design expects the <code>SubnetActor</code> to send <cod=
e>msg.value</code>, use <code>require(msg.value =3D=3D genesisCircSupply + =
collateral, "Incorrect deposit")</code>.</p>
